le ways, and that individuals can find ways of evading or easing its constraints.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aErotic literature, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 0aSex in literature. 4aGender Studies. 4aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171870040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501718700423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501718700/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles